Acasti Pharma Inc.


            
            Acasti Pharma, Inc. engages in the research, development, and commercialization of krill oil-based forms of omega-3 phospholipid therapies. It seeks to treat certain cardiometabolic disorders such as abnormalities in blood lipids, also known as dyslipidemia. It sproduct candidate, CaPre, is being developed to treat severe hypertriglyceridemia. The company was founded by Henri Harland on February 1, 2002 and is headquartered in Laval, Canada.

            
